<task id="038" project="sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix">
  <metadata>
    <title>DI registration count baseline + Outcome E expected delta</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>20 minutes</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>bff-api, baseline, di, adr-010, phase-3</tags>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Read-only grep across DI modules; no file conflicts with Group E siblings</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Capture the DI registration count for `Sprk.Bff.Api` as the Phase 3 baseline. This makes the ADR-010 binding enforceable rather than aspirational: instead of a vague "no-worsen" promise, Phase 4 tasks can verify their delta against this measurable baseline, and the Phase 4 gate (task 054) confirms Outcome E delivers a NET REDUCTION (the only outcome that should change the count materially).

    Background: ADR-010 targets ≤15 non-framework DI registrations. The BFF is known to be at ~99+ (a separate architectural project will address). THIS project commits to: (a) tracking the exact baseline, (b) verifying no Phase 4 candidate worsens it, (c) confirming Outcome E delivers net reduction (facade adds ~4 interfaces; consumer migrations should remove ~59 direct injections → expected net delta around -55).
  </prompt>

  <role>.NET DI / module-structure analyst.</role>

  <goal>
    File `baseline/di-registrations.txt` containing:
    1. Total count of `AddSingleton` + `AddScoped` + `AddTransient` + `AddHostedService` calls in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/`
    2. Per-module breakdown (one row per `*Module.cs` file)
    3. Per-lifetime breakdown
    4. Expected post-Outcome-E delta (facade introductions vs consumer migrations)
    5. Comparison to ADR-010 target (≤15) — documents the known gap
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="di-modules">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/</file>
    <file purpose="program">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
    <file purpose="adr">.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">≤15 non-framework registrations (target; known violation at ~99+)</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md §Out of Scope">Fixing the ADR-010 violation is NOT in scope; this task ONLY measures</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (this task)">Establishes the measurable baseline that makes ADR-010 binding enforceable in Phase 4</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Without this measurement, the ADR-010 "no-worsen" claim is unenforceable — Phase 4 changes could silently add registrations and we'd have no way to detect it. This task converts the aspirational binding into a measurable one. Task 054 (Phase 4 gate) then verifies the actual delta against the prediction here.

      Outcome E's expected impact on DI count:
      - Task 046 ADDS: 4+ facade interfaces (`IBriefingAi`, `IInvoiceAi`, `IRecordMatchingAi`, `IWorkspacePrefillAi`) plus their implementations → +8 registrations (or fewer if a single PublicContractsModule registers them collectively)
      - Tasks 047–050 REMOVE: ~59 direct consumer-side injections of `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` (these were already registered in AnalysisServicesModule, so the REGISTRATIONS don't change — only the INJECTION SITES do)
      - Task 051 (handler relocation): namespace change only; DI registration unchanged (JobType string dispatch by name)
      - **Net expected delta: ~+4 to +8 from facade interfaces; consumer migration changes injection sites but not registration count**

      Correction: the "net reduction" framing in prior planning was wrong. The DI REGISTRATION count goes UP by the facade additions; what goes DOWN is the consumer-side DEPENDENCY count (constructor parameter count across 59 files). Both metrics matter but they're distinct. This task measures registrations; the FR-E2 grep acceptance (task 053) measures consumer-side dependencies.
    </background>
    <dependencies><dependency task="022" status="not-started">Phase 2 gate</dependency></dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">`mkdir -p projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/baseline/`</step>
    <step order="2">Total count: `grep -rEc "\.Add(Singleton|Scoped|Transient|HostedService)\b" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/ | awk -F: '{sum+=$2} END {print sum}'`</step>
    <step order="3">Per-module breakdown: same grep per `*Module.cs` file</step>
    <step order="4">Per-lifetime breakdown: count each of Singleton / Scoped / Transient / HostedService separately</step>
    <step order="5">Also grep `Program.cs` for any direct DI calls outside modules</step>
    <step order="6">Write `baseline/di-registrations.txt` with: total, per-module table, per-lifetime table, ADR-010 gap notation (current vs ≤15), expected Outcome E delta calculation</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md task 038 status</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="git">grep</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="report">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/baseline/di-registrations.txt</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Total DI registration count captured (single number)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-module breakdown present (one row per *Module.cs)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-lifetime breakdown present (Singleton / Scoped / Transient / HostedService)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ADR-010 gap documented (current count vs ≤15 target)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Expected Outcome E delta calculation present and explained</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
